node.text: This week on Bite Size, Resident Baking BFF @emcdowell is exploring the sweet and savory world of tarte tatins (or, as she calls it, upside-down pies!). Follow along as she shares various techniques, tips, and challenges with this delicious dish. Watch the newest episode at the link in bio for a sweet time! #f52community

node.title: How to Bake Tarte Tatin with Erin McDowell - Bite Size

node.text: Shout out to tomatoes for being delicious in all forms, including two of our favorites: grilled and marinated! 🍅 Watch as @amandahesser takes this iconic summer fruit to the next level using @itsalislagle’s Grilled Marinated Tomatoes recipe complete with lime, fish sauce, chili, and shallot. Get the recipe at the link in bio. #f52community

node.title: Grilled Marinated Tomatoes - Amanda Messes Up in the Kitchen

node.text: Today we’re hanging out with @grossypelosi in his Brooklyn kitchen, making a dessert he ate all summer as a child: his Grandma’s Italian cream-filled sponge cake! Plus, as a treat, he’s showing three different ways you can decorate the top (a big dollop of whipped cream is required for all!). Grab the full recipe at the link in bio. #f52community

node.title: Grandma’s Italian Sponge Cake with Dan Pelosi - At Home With Us

node.text: We're back in @amandahesser's kitchen, and today, she's making fall-off-the-bone ribs that are sure to score serious points at your next barbeque. They get slathered in a rub mixture of sea salt, paprika, ground coffee beans, and peppercorns, then slow-cooked for 7 hours (for maximum flavor!). Grab Resident @ladyandpups's recipe for Coffee-Crusted Barbecue Beef Ribs at the link in bio. #f52community

node.title: Coffee-Crusted Barbecue Beef Ribs - Amanda Messes Up in the Kitchen

node.text: Meet your new favorite pasta dish: @mateo.zielonka's fennel, shallot, and capers chitarra recipe! From his book "Pasta Man" this dish is all about fresh flavors with homemade semolina pasta, shallots, fennel, capers, and served with plenty of nutritional yeast. Grab the recipe at the link in bio. #f52community

node.title: Fennel, Shallot & Caper Tagliatelle with Mateo Zielonka - at Home with Us

node.text: Resident Baking BFF @emcdowell wasn't completely sold on the idea of no-bake cheesecake but quickly came to realize it's unique in its own way and is the perfect refreshing dessert for summer! node.title: How to Make Cheesecakes - Bake It Up a Notch with Erin McDowell

node.text: Grilled shrimp and romesco is the duo we needed in our lives this summer! In this flavor-packed recipe from @emily_c99, romesco doubles as both a marinade and dipping sauce (!!!) for the shrimp. Add this dish to your summer dinner table at the link in bio. 📸: @mj_kroeger

node.text: Carved from natural volcanic stone, this molcajete is the traditional Mexican way of grinding sauces and prepping guacamole. The rough surface helps crush your ingredients more thoroughly, releasing their oils and juices (that means more flavor). Another bonus: This one’s roomy—about 8 1/2 inches in diameter—so you can prep a whole batch of salsa if you please. Get yours at the link in our bio. 📸: @jamesransom_nyc

node.text: Shout out to tomatoes for being delicious in all forms, including two of our favorites: grilled and marinated! 🍅 Watch as @amandahesser takes this iconic summer fruit to the next level using @itsalislagle’s Grilled Marinated Tomatoes recipe complete with lime, fish sauce, chili, and shallot.
